## INSTALL

you need to have twisted installed:
zypper in python-twisted

cp kippo.cfg.dist kippo.cfg

logging to hpfeeds:
cd kippo/dblog
wget https://raw.github.com/rep/hpfeeds/master/appsupport/kippo/hpfeeds.py

edit database_hpfeeds section in cfg

logging to mysql:
(from http://bruteforce.gr/logging-kippo-events-using-mysql-db.html)
mysql -u root -p
> CREATE DATABASE kippo;
> GRANT ALL ON kippo.* TO 'kippo'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';
> exit

mysql -u kippo -p
> USE kippo;
> source ./doc/sql/mysql.sql;
> exit

uncomment database_mysql secion in cfg

## RUN

./start.sh
